job_tasks.phrase: Build Interactive Front-End Features: Develop engaging and dynamic features like an image editing canvas that gives users precise control over Generative AI outputs.
job_tasks.justification: This phrase describes the development of user-facing application features, a core aspect of software development.

job_tasks.phrase: Integrate with Backend: Collaborate closely with our backend team to integrate the front-end with the Python FastAPI backend, ensuring seamless communication between client-side and server-side.
job_tasks.justification: This describes the integration of front-end with backend systems, which falls under software development.

job_tasks.phrase: Improve User Flows: Refine the registration and login process, making it smoother and more user-friendly.
job_tasks.justification: Improving user interface and flows is a key part of front-end software development.

job_tasks.phrase: User Activity Tracking: Implement tracking features using tools like June and Google Analytics to gather actionable insights and optimize user experience.
job_tasks.justification: Implementing tracking features and analytics integration is a software development task.

job_tasks.phrase: Enhance Onboarding: Revamp the user onboarding process, integrating customer service tools and demo videos to ensure users can quickly understand and navigate the platform.
job_tasks.justification: Revamping and integrating tools for user onboarding is a software development responsibility.

classification.rationale: This job primarily focuses on front-end development using standard web technologies like React.JS, Next.JS, and Node.JS. While it mentions 'Generative AI outputs', the core responsibilities do not involve building, fine-tuning, or deploying generative models themselves, nor do they indicate deep involvement with LLM frameworks or RAG systems. It leans more towards the application of AI outputs rather than the engineering of the AI models.
